Isomorphic strings:---Tricky
/**
 * @param {string} s
 * @param {string} t
 * @return {boolean}
 */
var isIsomorphic = function(s, t) {
   if (s.length !== t.length) return false;

    let mapST={};
    let mapTS={};
    //If for loop executes properly, then return true
    for(let i=0;i<s.length;i++){
        let a=s[i];
        let b=t[i];
       
        if(mapST[a] && mapST[a]!==b) return false;
        if(mapTS[b] && mapTS[b]!==a) return false;
        mapST[a]=b;
        mapTS[b]=a;
    }
    
   return true;
};

⏱ Time Complexity
O(n)

Single pass through the string.

Space complexity:

O(1)

(max 256 ASCII characters)

💡 Interview Tip (Senior dev level explanation)

Isomorphic strings require bijective mapping between characters of both strings. We maintain two hash maps to ensure one-to-one mapping consistency.
